<page xmlns="http://projectmallard.org/1.0/"
      type="topic"
      id="filemenu">
<info>
  <link type="guide" xref="menus"/> 
</info>
<title>The File Menu</title>
<list>
	<item><gui>New</gui><p>Empty the current grid and enter "design" mode</p></item>
	<item><gui>Load ...</gui>
	<list>
		<item><gui>Puzzle</gui><p>Shows a file selection dialogue with the puzzles in the current game directory.  By default gnonogram game files are shown but the filter can be changed to Picto games.  If the directory is changed then that becomes the default game directory.</p></item>
		<item><gui>Unfinished</gui><p>If the program was closed before finishing a puzzle (or the unfinished puzzle manually saved) then the partially completed puzzle is reloaded and solving mode entered</p></item>	
	</list></item>
	<item><gui>Save ...</gui>
		<list>
		<item><gui>Puzzle</gui><p>Shows a file <gui>Save As</gui> dialogue in the current game directory.  By default gnonogram game files are shown but the filter can be changed to Picto games.  If the directory is changed then that becomes the default game directory.</p></item>
		<item><gui>Unfinished</gui><p>If the program was closed before finishing a puzzle (or the unfinished puzzle manually saved) then the partially completed puzzle is reloaded and solving mode entered</p></item>	
	</list></item>
	<item><gui>Save as Pictogame</gui><p></p></item>
	<item><gui>Quit</gui><p></p></item>
</list>
</page>
